gpt_response:

By counting the number of each type of atom in the molecular formula, we can determine the molecular formula of CN1N=C(N=N1)CC(CO)CO. Based on the structure of the molecule, we can determine that there are 5 carbon atoms (C), 4 nitrogen atoms (N), and 4 oxygen atoms (O) present in the molecule.

Therefore, the molecular formula of CN1N=C(N=N1)CC(CO)CO is C5N4O4.
